The Federal Government has rolled out an Autogas programme called the National Gas Expansion Programme aimed at deepening domestic usage of natural gas in its various forms.  Speaking virtually from the Presidential villa, Abuja, President Muhammadu Buhari said the programme is in line with his administration's plan to make gas the first choice source of cheaper and cleaner energy which will attract investors and lead to job creation. Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the programme which  involves the conversion of fuel-powered cars, generators from petrol to gas is expected to go live in all states of the Federation.  While live at the Lugbe LPG dispensing station launching, the Minister of State for Petroleum, Timipre Sylva handed over the keys to five buses running on CNG to the Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC)following the directives of Mr President. The Managing Director of Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), Mele Kyari; said the Autogas program is expected to deliver at least one million vehicle conversions by the end of 2021.